          "date": "2013-11-13 18:31:46.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-4248 tests: parametrize racer progs and file_create.sh",
        "message": "LU-4248 tests: parametrize racer progs and file_create.sh\n\nIn racer/racer.sh allow RACER_PROGS to be overridden from the\nenvironment. In racer/file_create.sh allow the block size, max block\ncount, and max stripe count to be overridden from the environment. Set\nthe default block size and max block count to the previously used\nvaules. Set the default the max stripe count to the number of\nOSTs. Use $((RANDOM % (max_stripe_count + 1))) for the stripe count\npassed to lfs setstripe, ensuring that fully striped files will be\noccasionally created.\n\nSigned-off-by: John L. Hammond <john.hammond@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Iffc0d821e815cf399224e537c6ac536b8a1e8569\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
